    <div class="post-container" id="fpc-2414515">
                      
		<div class="post" id="post-2414515">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,2414515)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-2414515">
																		Re: Just wondering...
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/qntm" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(571081); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=571081&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610225351" alt="qntm" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=571081)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/qntm" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(571081); return false;" >qntm</a></span> <span class="odate time_1448723715 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">28 Nov 2015 15:15</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2414515">
									

<p>SCP-3125 is the designation for the root cause of numerous phenomena in the Foundation universe, of which:</p>
<ul>
<li>some are anomalous</li>
<li>some have antimemetic properties</li>
<li>some are known to the Foundation</li>
<li>some are known the Antimemetics division</li>
<li>some have appeared in these Tales.</li>
</ul>
<p>(All of the sets are different and overlap to different degrees.) SCP-3125 itself <em>hasn't</em> been directly mentioned before, but many of its manifestations have. However, <strong>SCP-3125 is definitely not the source of <em>all</em> antimemetic phenomena</strong>, any more than the Earth is the source of all gravity. In my view this kind of catchall explanation shrinks the universe and makes it less interesting. It also constrains the storytelling possibilities as we move forward. There need to be other ways to get antimemes, otherwise that's just dull and it ties everybody's hands.</p>
<p>(Did you notice that SCP-3125 is a monster which eats people who try to find a common origin for too many other SCPs? This is deliberate!)</p>
<p>In this Tale, Wheeler claims (and she is <em>probably</em> correct, although not infallible) that the following are manifestations/symptoms/injuries to our reality ultimately traceable back to SCP-3125:</p>
<ul>
<li>SCP-1425</li>
<li>SCP-033</li>
<li>SCP-2828</li>
<li>the massive invisible spider entity which ate Marness in &quot;Unforgettable, That's What You Are&quot;</li>
</ul>
<p>I will also go on record saying that</p>
<ul>
<li>Clay in &quot;We Need To Talk About Fifty-Five&quot;</li>
<li>Grey in &quot;Introductory Antimemetics&quot;</li>
</ul>
<p>originate from SCP-3125; in fact, they were antimemetic weapons deployed against the Antimemetics division as part of this ongoing war (to which the division was oblivious at the time).</p>
<p>I thought about this a little and I'm going to go ahead and say</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>The Contagious Murder Of Bartholomew Hughes</strong></li>
</ul>
<p><strong><em>is</em> another manifestation of SCP-3125</strong>. Note that this murder took place &quot;seven years&quot; ago, i.e. in 2008. This was the year that SCP-055 was originally contained. It's also the year that global antimemetic science apparently peaked, as Wheeler implies in this Tale. That seems to be the year that (this iteration of) the war began.</p>

							</div>

								
