					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/werdna" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2161854); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2161854&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610225351" alt="werdna" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2161854)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/werdna" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2161854); return false;" >werdna</a></span> <span class="odate time_1449032290 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">02 Dec 2015 04:58</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2416270">
									

<p>I love this tale, and I love the anti-memetics concept and what you've done with it; it adds an extra layer of depth to the Foundation universe without feeling forced, cheesy, or cliche, especially compared to certain other things on the site, like certain GOIs.</p>
<p>Horror comes from fear of the unknown, so writing tales about the unknowable is the next logical step. I think that's why this all works so well.</p>
<p>Your focus on the Foundation as a scientific organization does wonders to maintain one's suspension of disbelief when reading stories like this.</p>
<p>I also like how SCP-055 was contained when it was published. Does this mean all the anti-memetic stories take place in real time (at the time of their publication)?</p>

							</div>

								
					
